The author of the article reflects on their time serving with Mike Enzi in the United States Senate. Despite being on different sides of the aisle, the author admires Enzi's decency, honor, and integrity. Enzi was an Eagle Scout, National Guardsman, small business owner, small-town mayor, and state legislator before becoming a U.S. Senator. He always remained connected to his roots in Wyoming and the people who elected him. The author expresses sadness at Enzi's passing and offers prayers for his family, friends, colleagues, and staff.